==English==
===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|en|yealm}}
===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|yelm}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġilm}}, {{m|ang|ġelm|t=handful}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*galmi}}, possibly ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵʰelh₃-|t=to flourish}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/jɛlm/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-yealm.wav|Audio (Southern England)}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|dialect}} A [[bundle]] of [[straw]] for [[thatch]]ing.
#* '''1952''', {{w|Louis Francis Salzman}}, ''Building in England'', p. 224:
#*: The thatcher then laid the ''' 'yelms' ''', or bunches of drawn straw, on the laths, beginning at the eaves and working up towards the ridge.
===Verb===
{{en-verb}}
# {{lb|en|dialect}} To [[prepare]] [[straw]] for use as [[thatch]].
#* '''1952''', {{w|Louis Francis Salzman}}, ''Building in England'', p. 224:
#*: The preparation of straw for thatch, which was known as ''' 'yelming' ''', consisted in damping it and 'drawing' it with a thatching-fork, or great comb, so as to get the straws parallel.
